{"title_page": "Institute for Advanced Strategic and Political Studies", "text_new": "The '''Institute for Advanced Strategic and Political Studies''' (IASPS) is an Israel-based [[think tank]] with an affiliated office in Washington, D.C. It was founded in 1984 by its president, Professor Robert Loewenberg.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://rightweb.irc-online.org/profile/1493.html|title=Institute for Advanced Strategic and Political Studies|date=September 14, 2006|website=Right Web|publisher=International Relations Center|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090211091843/http://rightweb.irc-online.org/profile/1493.html|archive-date=February 11, 2009|url-status=|access-date=September 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Political stance==\nIn the US, IASPS has connections with the [[neoconservative]] movement in American politics. The institute is notable for its [[A Clean Break: A New Strategy for Securing the Realm|Clean Break]] report which is considered \"a kind of [[Israel-United States relations|US-Israeli]] [[neoconservative]] [[manifesto]]\" according to journalist [[Jason Vest]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thenation.com/doc.mhtml?i=20020902&s=vest|title=The Men From JINSA and CSP|last=Vest|first=Jason|date=August 15, 2002|website=[[The Nation]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050417040513/http://www.thenation.com/doc.mhtml%3Fi%3D20020902%26s%3Dvest|archive-date=April 17, 2005|url-status=live|access-date=August 31, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.iasps.org Official website]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Institute For Advanced Strategic And Political Studies}}\n[[Category:Foreign policy and strategy think tanks in the United States]]\n[[Category:Political and economic think tanks in the United States]]\n[[Category:Foreign policy political advocacy groups in the United States]]\n[[Category:New Right organizations (United States)]]\n[[Category:Think tanks established in 1984]]\n[[Category:Israel\u2013United States relations]]\n[[Category:United States\u2013Middle Eastern relations]]\n[[Category:Middle Eastern studies in the United States]]\n[[Category:Jewish political organizations]]\n[[Category:Foreign relations of Israel]]\n", "text_old": "The '''Institute for Advanced Strategic and Political Studies''' (IASPS) is an Israel-based [[think tank]] with an affiliated office in Washington, D.C. It was founded in 1984 by its president, Professor Robert Loewenberg.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://rightweb.irc-online.org/profile/1493.html|title=Institute for Advanced Strategic and Political Studies|date=September 14, 2006|website=Right Web|publisher=International Relations Center|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090211091843/http://rightweb.irc-online.org/profile/1493.html|archive-date=February 11, 2009|url-status=|access-date=September 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Political stance==\nIn the US, IASPS has connections with the [[neoconservative]] movement in American politics. The institute is notable for its [[A Clean Break: A New Strategy for Securing the Realm|Clean Break]] report which is considered \"a kind of [[Israel-United States relations|US-Israeli]] [[neoconservative]] [[manifesto]]\" according to journalist [[Jason Vest]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thenation.com/doc.mhtml?i=20020902&s=vest|title=The Men From JINSA and CSP|last=Vest|first=Jason|date=August 15, 2002|website=[[The Nation]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050417040513/http://www.thenation.com/doc.mhtml%3Fi%3D20020902%26s%3Dvest|archive-date=April 17, 2005|url-status=live|access-date=August 31, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.iasps.org Official website]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Institute For Advanced Strategic And Political Studies}}\n[[Category:Foreign policy and strategy think tanks in the United States]]\n[[Category:Political and economic think tanks in the United States]]\n[[Category:Foreign policy political advocacy groups in the United States]]\n[[Category:New Right 