{"title_page": "Gaye Alassane", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n|name                = Gaye\n|image               = \n|fullname            = Gaye Alassane\n|birth_date          = 1975\n|birth_place         = [[Mali]]\n|height              = \n|currentclub         = \n|clubnumber          =\n|position            = \n|youthyears1         = \n|youthclubs1         = \n|years1              = \n|clubs1 = [[Batavia]] | clubs2 = [[Tiong Bahru CSC]] | clubs3 = [[Woodlands Wellington FC | Wellington FC]] | clubs4 = [[Tampines Rovers FC]] | clubs5 = [[Gombak United FC]] | clubs6 = [[Tampines Rovers 1951]] | clubs7= [[1 Tanah Merah FC]] (5v5)\n|nationalyears1      = \n|nationalteam1       = \n|nationalcaps1       = \n|nationalgoals1      = \n|club-update         = \n|nationalteam-update = \n|managerclubs1 = [[List of football clubs in Singapore | Changi Village SRC]]\n|managerclubs2 = [[Yishun FC]]\n}}\nGaye Alassane is a Mali-born Singaporean football coach. He has played professional football with top-flight clubs , [[Tiong Bahru CSC]], [[Woodlands Wellington FC | Wellington FC]], [[Tampines Rovers FC]] and [[Gombak United FC]]. Upon his departure from the professional [[S.League]], he went on to play at the [[Singapore National Football League]] club [[Tampines Rovers 1951]]. He then went on to play in the top flight amateur ESPZEN 5v5 league club for [[1 Tanah Merah FC]]. He is currently the head coach of [[Yishun FC]].\n==References==\n\n\n*[https://mustsharenews.com/gaye-alassane-citizenship/ Who Is Gaye Alassane, The Former Footballer Who Had His Citizenship Stripped For Match Fixing?]\n*[https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/gaye-alassane-singapore-citizenship-s-league-player-10474548 Former S-League player Gaye Alassane to keep Singapore citizenship despite match-fixing]\n*[https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/sport/what-next-for-former-s-league-footballer-gaye-alassane-9477942 What next for former S-League footballer Gaye Alassane?]\n*\n", "text_ol