ates House of Representatives|U.S. House]] from [[California's 33rd congressional district|CA-33]] in [[2014 United States House of Representatives elections in California#District 33|2014]] \n|| {{hs|CA}}{{flag|California}}\n|| {{dts|2019|01|28}}<br>{{small|Exploratory committee: {{dts|2018|11|15}}\u2013<br>{{dts|2019|01|27}}}}\n|| {{dts|2020|01|10}}<br>{{small|(endorsed Sanders)}}\n|| {{Hs|2019-01-28}} [[File:Marianne Williamson 2020 presidential campaign logo.svg|frameless|90x90px]]<br>[[Marianne Williamson 2020 presidential campaign|Campaign]]\n||<ref name=williamson>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbclosangeles.com/news/local/Marianne-Williamson-Announces-Presidential-Candidacy-505014341.html|title=Author Marianne Williamson Announces Presidential Candidacy|website=[[NBC]]|date=January 29, 2019|access-date=November 1, 2019}}</ref>\n|-id=Castro\n! {{hs|Castro}}[[File:Julian Castro 2019 crop.jpg|frameless|x100px]]<br>[[Julian Castro|Juli\u00e1n Castro]]\n| {{dts|1974|9|16}}<br>(age {{age nts|1974|9|16}})<br>[[San Antonio|San Antonio, Texas]] \n|| '''[[United States Secretary of Housing and Urban Development|Secretary of Housing and Urban Development]] (2014\u20132017)'''<br>[[List of mayors of San Antonio|Mayor]] of [[San Antonio]], [[Texas]] (2009\u20132014) \n|| {{hs|TX}}{{flag|Texas}}\n|| {{dts|2019|1|12}}\n|| {{dts|2020|01|02}} {{small|(endorsed Warren)}}\n|| {{Hs|2019-01-12}} [[File:Julian Castro 2020 presidential campaign logo.svg|frameless|90x90px]]<br>[[Juli\u00e1n Castro 2020 presidential campaign|Campaign]]\n||<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/02/us/politics/julian-castro-dropping-out.html|title=Juli\u00e1n Castro Ends Presidential Run: \u2018It Simply Isn\u2019t Our Time\u2019|first1=Jennifer|last1=Medina|first2=Matt|last2=Stevens|date=January 2, 2020|work=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref>\n|-id=Harris\n! {{hs|Harris}}[[File:Kamala Harris by Gage Skidmore 2.jpg|x100px]]<br>[[Kamala Harris]]\n| {{dts|1964|10|20}}<br>(age {{age nts|1964|10|20}}