nz Kraus, New York<br> Total votes: 52\n*Rita Krichevsky, New Jersey<br> Total votes: 23\n*Raymond Michael Moroz, New York<br> Total votes: 8\n*[[Sam Sloan]], New York<br> Total votes: 34\n*David John Thistle, Massachusetts<br> Total votes: 53\n*Thomas James Torgesen, New York<br> Total votes: 30\n*[[Robby Wells]], Georgia<br> Total votes: 45\n{{div col end}}\n\u2021<small>Roque De La Fuente III is the son of perennial candidate [[Rocky De La Fuente]] and is not the same individual.</small>\n\n=== Not on the ballot anywhere ===\nIndividuals who did not meet the criteria to become major candidates have either formally terminated their campaigns or did not attempt to get on the ballot in a single contest:\n* [[Harry Braun]], renewable energy consultant and researcher; Democratic nominee for [[United States House of Representatives|U.S. representative]] from [[Arizona's 1st congressional district|AZ-01]] in [[1984 United States House of Representatives elections#Arizona|1984]] and [[1986 United States House of Representatives elections#Arizona|1986]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://docquery.fec.gov/pdf/531/201712200300182531/201712200300182531.pdf|title=Statement of Candidacy by Harry William Braun III|date=December 5, 2017|website=[[Federal Election Commission]]|access-date=January 13, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171223215748/http://docquery.fec.gov/pdf/531/201712200300182531/201712200300182531.pdf|archive-date=December 23, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://braunforpresident.us/|title=Harry Braun for President|website=Harry Braun for President Committee 2020|accessdate=April 27, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190508044454/https://braunforpresident.us/|archive-date=May 8, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Ami Horowitz]], conservative activist and documentary filmmaker ''(endorsed [[Donald Trump|Trump]])''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://docquery.fec.gov/pdf/227/201905029149627227/201905029149627227.pdf|title=Statement of Can