01-11}} [[File:Tulsi Gabbard 2020 presidential campaign logo black.svg|frameless|90x90px]]<br>[[Tulsi Gabbard 2020 presidential campaign|Campaign]]\nFEC filing<ref>{{cite web |url=http://docquery.fec.gov/pdf/762/201901119143806762/201901119143806762.pdf |title=Statement of Candidacy by Tulsi Gabbard |date=January 11, 2019 |website=[[Federal Election Commission]] |access-date=January 21, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190114044534/http://docquery.fec.gov/pdf/762/201901119143806762/201901119143806762.pdf |archive-date=January 14, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/01/11/politics/tulsi-gabbard-van-jones/index.html|title=Tulsi Gabbard says she will run for president in 2020|last1=Kelly|first1=Caroline|accessdate=January 11, 2019|date=January 12, 2019|work=CNN|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190111233547/https://www.cnn.com/2019/01/11/politics/tulsi-gabbard-van-jones/index.html|archive-date=January 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|- id=\"Warren\"\n! {{hs|Warren}}[[File:Elizabeth Warren by Gage Skidmore (cropped).jpg|x100px]]<br>[[Elizabeth Warren]]\n| {{dts|1949|6|22}}<br>(age {{age nts|1949|6|22}})<br>[[Oklahoma City|Oklahoma City, Oklahoma]]||'''[[United States Senate|U.S. senator]] from [[Massachusetts]] (2013\u2013present)'''\n||{{hs|MA}}{{Flag|Massachusetts}}\n|{{Date table sorting|February 9, 2019}}<br><small>Exploratory Committee:</small> <small>December 31, 2018</small>\n|{{dts|2020|3|5}}\n|{{Hs|2019-02-09}} [[File:Elizabeth Warren 2020 presidential campaign logo.svg|frameless|90x90px]]<br>[[Elizabeth Warren 2020 presidential campaign|Campaign]]<br>FEC filing<ref>{{cite web |url=http://docquery.fec.gov/pdf/256/201902130300267256/201902130300267256.pdf |title=Statement of Candidacy by Elizabeth Warren |date=February 9, 2019 |website=[[Federal Election Commission]] |access-date=February 18, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190218081926/http://docquery.fec.gov/pdf/256/20190213030